Make sure you wash your hands well
We all know that they need to be washed (e.g. after coming home or before meals).
But not everyone knows that in order to actually get rid of germs, you have to do it the right way.
This is especially important now that autumn infections are approaching.
It takes at least 30–40 seconds for washing to sufficiently remove dangerous bacteria and viruses from our hands
Yet most of us wash them less!
All it takes is warm water and simple soap – it is not true that it must be antibacterial (many doctors even advise them against it).
By washing, we rub not only the bottoms and the tops of the hand, but also: finger tips (attached or individually) – rub them with circular motions on the inside of the second hand, the spaces between the fingers (strip your hands, rubbing your fingers against each other), thumbs – each thumb we hold the other hand and in such a embrace we spin it a moment to the right and left.
In an emergency (when you cannot wash your hands) we should wipe our hands with a wet handkerchief and then use antibacterial gel (in drugstores, from PLN 5).
After using the public toilet, do not touch the hand-washed handles or doors (recommendation of the Main Sanitary Inspectorate).
Open it through a paper towel.
Iran's president says he turned down the U.S. call, Donald Trump denies
Tehran did not engage with the American side during the United Nations General Assembly in New York City, despite the Americans' offer to abolish sanctions," stated Iran's President Hasan Rowhani on Friday.
U.S. President Donald Trump commented that it was the Iranian side that asked for the restrictions to be lifted, which he refused to do.
According to Iran's President Hasan Rowhani, the Americans proposed the abolition of all sanctions imposed on Tehran in exchange for entering into negotiations on a new international agreement.
It would regulate both Iran's nuclear program and the ballistic missile program.
Rowhani: Iran will not make talks in the atmosphere of maximum pressure
The President of Iran stated that he did not agree to take these talks due to the "toxic atmosphere".
He stated that he had met with American diplomats because he had submitted to the teachings of France, Germany and Great Britain.
However, he stressed that Iran would not engage in talks in an atmosphere of "maximum pressure".
"And even if we want to negotiate with Americans in 5+1 format, no one can predict what the end result will be," Rowhani said.
A day earlier, the Iranian leader said that he did not exclude talks with the US, and the European parties to the nuclear agreement had abandoned favouring American sanctions against Iran.
He added that the sanctions imposed on Iran following the U.S. withdrawal from the nuclear agreement "are a prerequisite that does not allow" dialogue to be established.
If we can lift this precondition and if America can lift sanctions and maximum pressure, then of course we can talk to America – he declared.
He added that he did not exclude a meeting with U.S. President Donald Trump, even though he did not agree to such a conversation during the past week during the UN General Assembly.
Trump: “Iran asked, I said no”
Donald Trump tweeted that he rejected the request of the Iranian side.
“Iran wanted me to lift the sanctions imposed on them so that we could meet.
Of course, I said no," tweeted the President of the United States.
Tension with an atomic agreement in the background
France, Germany and the United Kingdom are trying to ease the tensions between Washington and Tehran to save in some form the 2015 deal with Iran, which they were signatories to.
It stated that in exchange for the abolition of economic sanctions, Iran would resign from the nuclear weapons programme and that the nuclear sector would be subject to control by the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA).
Since the withdrawal of the US from the agreement in May 2015, its remaining signatories have repeatedly confirmed that they want to maintain the agreement in force.
Nothing's worked out so far.
Washington uses the tactics of exerting maximum pressure on Iran, and sanctions also include full embargo on Iranian oil.
Tehran announced that if it did not receive a licence to export raw material, it would limit its obligations under the agreement every 60 days.
