The Senate has decided on key laws
The Senate adopted without amendment the Act on the disclosure of the assets of the families of the most important government officials and the flights of the most important persons in the state.
52 senators voted in favour of the amendment of the Act on the property of families of government officials – without amendments – and 14 were against, three abstained.
The Senators therefore decided to reject the 12 amendments tabled during the Wednesday debate by Senator PO Sławomir Rybicki.
According to him, the amendments were intended to "civilise" and limit the scope of the information provided in the statement on the property situation of own children, children of the spouse, children adopted to cases where children remain in a common household with the person obliged to make a statement.
The law on the disclosure of the assets of the families of the most important public officials whose project was created at the Prime Minister's office was passed by the Sejm on 11 September.
The rules assume that, among others, the Prime Minister, ministers, MPs, MEPs, senators, presidents: the Constitutional Court, the Supreme Administrative Court and the Supreme Court, as well as persons who are at the head of other state institutions, will be required to include in their declaration the personal assets of spouses, children and persons who remain in common life.
The Senate also did not propose amendments to the Act on flights of the most important persons in the state.
It regulates what flights have HEAD status and who may be on board government aircraft along with the most important persons in the state.
The Act also specifies who is responsible for keeping the Central Flight Register.
The bill – without amendments – was favoured by 55 senators, 12 opposed, four abstained.
According to the Act, every flight of the President will be a flight "executed in an official mission".
On flights, the President will be able to accompany family members and other persons invited by the President.
On the other hand, the official Prime Minister and Speakers of the Sejm and the Senate will only fly "to perform tasks directly related to the function."
The Act also specifies a list of persons who may accompany the most important persons in the country during the flight.
