According to the newspaper, disregarding a specific conduct order issued by a police officer is to be a new type of misconduct, threatened by fines, detentions, or restrictions on freedom.
The political unionists want to introduce such a change.
The idea went to the Parliamentary Committee on Petitions.
"The case is serious, because already every year more than half a million misdemeanor cases go to Polish courts", we read.
The "Rzeczpospolita" has determined that the petition, which the Independent Union of Police is writing to Members on the amendment of the Code of Offences, has a chance to succeed.
The petitioners propose a new wording of Article 54a of the Code of Offence.
It would read: "Whoever does not submit to the demand or order of a public officer, issued within the limits and under the provisions of the Act, is subject to imprisonment, fine or restriction of liberty."
"Par. 3 of this provision speaks of an identical penalty for those who fail to follow orders, prevent or impede the performance of their duties," the journal states.
